Title: Object: Iter Jacobi in Egyptum
Series: Knowsley Gallery
Description: Jacob's journey into Egypt, after Castiglione: at centre a servant presenting a treasure chest to a turbaned man mounted on a horse; game birds, pots, vessels and other utensils scattered all over the foreground; on the left, sheep and a donkey loaded with barrels and pots; on the right, two men leading a horse to the left. 1728 Etching
